    • isZonedDateTimeCompatible

      public boolean isZonedDateTimeCompatible()
      Tests whether an aggregate is friendly with DateTime columns. Because DateTime columns have a companion TZ column to maintain the timezone information, aggregates that cannot be ordered essentially are not usable. This method simply wraps isOrderable() in case we later need to make some modifications, i.e., the isTimeZoneCompatible is semantically different enough from isOrderable that we didn't want to alias them.
